

BASH = Bourne Again Shell

A CLI or Command Line Interpreter for the Unix system.

Eg. Linux is Unix-like system

Why use Command Line?
> Better control

Can create hidden folders

-------

Commands:

$ls (List everything)
$cd (Change Directory)
$cd ~ (takes back to route directory)
up & down button will take you to previous commands used

hold cntrl+a goes to beginning of command line
hold cntrl+e goes to end of command line
hold cntrl+u to clear entire line 

mkdir (name) - creates new folder
cd (name) - goes to that directory
open -a (application) .app (name)
rm (name of document) - deletes the text file
pwd - print working directory, tells you you entire path & folder location
rm -r (name) - removes the whole directory

